Tofu Katsu - really versatile and can be enjoyed in so many ways! I‚Äôll share the katsu recipe below!¬†üëáüèºthis Tofu Katsu with a Japanese Curry is just one way you can enjoy your tofu katsu‚Äîfor this one, I used curry sauce I got from a Japanese store (you can look for the brand S&B that sells curry in cubes) and just added some potatoes, bell peppers, and carrots. Served with some steamed Japanese rice of course üçõ 
Tofu Katsu
(Makes 4 katsu)
1 240g block fresh extra firm tofu¬†
1/4 tsp salt, or to taste*¬†
Canola oil, for frying (*Note: feel free to adjust the seasoning as needed. I had mine with curry sauce, which was already flavorful so I didn‚Äôt want the dish to be too salty or anything)

Batter¬†
1/4 cup flour
1/2 tbsp + 1 tsp cornstarch¬†
1/2 tsp baking powder
1/2 tsp salt
1/4 cup room temp. water

Breading¬†
1 cup japanese breadcrumbs, or more as needed

1. Drain water from the tofu by wrapping them in paper towels and then placing a heavy flat surface (a board or plate) on top of each. Leave for 15 minutes until water has been absorbed by the towels.
2. Slice each tofu into two 3/4-inch thick square slabs. Sprinkle with salt as needed.
3. Prepare the batter by mixing all the ingredients until smooth. This will be a really thick batter. In another plate or tray, add the breadcrumbs.¬†
4. Place each tofu in the batter then coat into the breadcrumbs. Repeat this step for the rest of the tofu.¬†
5. Heat the oil in a frying pan. Once hot (you can test this by putting a little bread crumbs), add in the tofu. Fry for around 6-8 minutes over medium heat until golden brown. Take out of the oil then turn off the heat.¬†
6. Let cool for 5-8 minutes then slice diagonally into strips

Other ways you can enjoy your tofu katsu:
1 - Katsu Sushi Sandwiches
2 - Japanese-Style Katsudon

1 clove garlic, minced
1/2 medium onion, chopped
1 can jackfruit in water, drained and rinsed (unsalted)
1/2 can coconut milk
2 tsp curry powder
1 tsp cumin
1/2 tsp turmeric
1/2 tsp paprika
1 tbsp tamari
2 tbsp tomato paste
Handful spinach
Rice or noodles to serve

Add the garlic and the onion to a non-stick frying pan and saut√© for 2 minutes, until fragrant. Add the jackfruit and saut√© for a further 5 minutes until lightly browned. At the last minute, stir in the spinach and serve immediately with rice or noodles.

Ingredients

3 oz lentil penne (dry weight)
3 large or 4 small collard green leaves, chopped
2 green onions, chopped
1 garlic clove, minced (optional)
1 large portobello mushroom cap, chopped
1/2 tsp liquid smoke or a pinch of smoked salt (optional)
1 tsp olive oil
1/2 tsp soy or Tamari sauce (optional)
1 cup of roasted butternut cashew sauce (recipe in the notes below)
Salt to taste
Freshly ground pepper
Instructions

Boil about 2-3 cups of water in an electric kettle (or a pot)*
In a pan, saut√© the green onion, mushroom and garlic in the olive oil over medium heat for 2-3 minutes before adding the soy sauce, liquid smoke and collard greens.
Mix well, then add the lentil penne and set a timer for 9 minutes.
Add just enough boiling water to the pan to cover the penne and keep stirring. Keep an eye on the pan and add a little more boiling water each time it starts to evaporate. You‚Äôll want there to be enough liquid to cook the penne, but not too much as you won‚Äôt be draining the pasta.
At the 7 minute mark, add the butter nut sauce to the pan and reduce heat to low. Keep stirring for the remaining 2 minutes. Add salt to taste Tip: If the sauce is too thin, add a little cornstarch and if it‚Äôs too thick, add a little water.
Serve topped with freshly ground pepper and enjoy!

Roasted Chickpeas and Avocado Toast by @twospoons.ca üíö
.

1 can (400 ml) chickpeas 
1/2 tsp paprika
2 tsp olive oil, plus more to drizzle
pinch sea salt
1 avocado

sea salt and pepper
.
.
1. Preheat oven to 400F/200C. Strain chickpeas and pat dry. Toss into a mixing bowl with paprika, olive oil and a generous pinch of sea salt. Mix to combine. Line a baking tray with parchment paper and pour chickpeas onto tray. Bake in oven for 5 minutes, or until lightly brown and sizzling.
2. Toast two slices sourdough bread. Scoop avocado onto bread and gently press down with a fork to mash and spread even. Sprinkle with sea salt and pepper. Top toast with roasted chickpeas. Optional to sprinkle with more sea salt, pepper and cayenne pepper. Lightly drizzle with olive oil. #bestofvegan

Do you worry about your child not eating enough? It's easy to think that we know how much food our kids need. But actually, we know WHAT food they need, not how much they need. ‚Å†‚†Ä
‚Å†‚†Ä
That's why I recommend serving small portions to start and letting them decide how much to eat...meaning, give them as many refills as they want, but don't force them to finish. ‚Å†‚†Ä
‚Å†‚†Ä
This is a best practice for teaching kids to eat the right amount for their body long term!‚Å†‚†Ä
‚Å†‚†Ä

Another idea to keep in mind. Combining different plant-based foods can help you get to your protein goals. (AD) For example, making a salad with 125g of @Sunrice Supergrains with half a tin of beans will give you almost 10g of plant protein. Add a handful of nuts for another 5g of protein. You‚Äôll also get plenty of plant diversity in this meal, which is great for gut microbiota (we should aim to get 30 different types of plant-based foods in our diet per week for a healthy gut). .

HEALTH-I-FIED GINGERBREAD MEN üéÑü§§
It‚Äôs the first day of December and that means 24 days until Christmas üéÖüèº So it‚Äôs time to start your Christmas cooking! üòÑ
.
These Health-i-fied Gingerbread Men are perfect to serve on Christmas Day or make as a cute little gift for friends and family! 
Here‚Äôs the recipe üëáüèº
.
‚ú®RECIPE: Health-i-fied Gingerbread Men 
Makes approx. 18 cookies
INGREDIENTS:
* 1 ¬º cups wholemeal flour
‚Ä¢ 1 tsp corn starch
‚Ä¢ ¬º tsp baking powder
‚Ä¢ 2 tsp ground ginger
‚Ä¢ ¬º tsp ground cinnamon
‚Ä¢ ¬º tsp ground nutmeg
‚Ä¢ ¬Ω tsp ground cloves
‚Ä¢ 1 tsp vanilla extract
‚Ä¢ 2 tbsp brown sugar
‚Ä¢ 2 tbsp olive or coconut oil (melted)
‚Ä¢ ¬º cup molasses
*Optional (Icing) - 10 tbsp. icing sugar, 2 tbsp. milk of choice
.
METHOD:
1. Preheat oven to 180 degrees Celsius
2. Combine dry ingredients in a large bowl, mix to combine.
3. Add into dry ingredients, along with vanilla and molasses to create a sticky cookie dough.
4. Roll out the cookie dough on a lightly floured surface and use a cookie cutter to shape into gingerbread men.
5. Place gingerbread cookies on a lined baking tray and bake for 10-15 minutes until golden.
6. *OPTIONAL: let cookies cool completely and decorate with royal icing or coconut.

Gluten-free pancakes made from oat flour - it‚Äôs basically oatmeal in pancake form, right?! ‚ò∫Ô∏è #saturdaybrunch #pancakes #bananapancakes #easyrecipes #glutenfreerecipes
‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä
INGREDIENTS
1 1/2 cup oats
2 teaspoons baking powder
1 teaspoon cinnamon
1/8 teaspoon salt
1 cup almond milk
1 egg 
1 ripe banana
1 teaspoon vanilla extract
1/2 cup chocolate chips
Coconut oil for cooking
INSTRUCTIONS
1. In a high-speed blender, place the oats, and blend until the oats become powder-like. Add the baking powder, cinnamon and salt to the blender and pulse once to combine. Transfer to a small bowl and set aside.
2. In the same blender, add the almond milk, egg, banana and vanilla extract, and blend until well combined.
3. Add the dry ingredients and mix until everything is well incorporated with no flour streaks. Some lumps in the batter are ok. Transfer batter to a bowl and fold in chocolate chips.
4. Scoop about 1/3 cup batter onto hot pan prepared with coconut oil and cook on medium heat for 2-3 minutes per side. Repeat for the remaining pancake batter.
5. Top with bananas and maple syrup, if desired and enjoy warm.

When we are talking about serving food, it is important not only to consider the food itself, but also the plate where you put the food. Although color is probably the most important factor in choosing the right dish, the shape and size can also affect the overall picture when serving food.

What do you prefer: Handpulled or knife cut noodles?
.
Knife cut noodles are made by shaving slices of noodles off a block of dough, creating ribbons of noodles of varying thicknesses and lengths. The beautiful thing about knife cut noodles is the texture of the noodles: since no two noodles are exactly the same, you get a slightly new and exciting experience on each bite.

Dark Chocolate Olive Oil Cake with whipped mascarpone & pomegranate arils featuring @carapelliusa‚Äôs Il Centenario Extra Virgin Olive Oil #carapelliambassador
.
I absolutely love using olive oil when I bake and this chocolate cake really highlights the beauty of @carapelliusa‚Äôs artfully crafted Il Centenario. This elegant extra virgin olive oil adds a pleasant bitterness & lovely fruitiness to this rich chocolate cake. Swirls of creamy whipped mascarpone get topped with deep ruby pomegranate arils for a gorgeous seasonal garnish that is perfectly festive for the holiday season!
.
This cake really highlights the beauty of @carapelliusa‚Äôs artfully crafted olive oil & will make for such a pleasant treat to share with friends & family during the holidays. Head to the link in my profile to learn more about @carapelliusa‚Äôs line of olive oils & grab the recipe for this amazing cake below!
.
INGREDIENTS
1-1/2 cups (180g) ap flour
2/3 cup (64g) unsweetened¬†Dutch processed cocoa powder
1-1/2 tsp baking soda
1/2 tsp kosher salt
3/4 cup (144g)sugar
2/3 cup (106g) dark brown sugar
1 tbsp instant espresso powder
1/2 cup olive oil
1 cup water, at room-temperature
2 tsp¬†pure vanilla extract
1 Tbsp apple cider vinegar
12 oz. mascarpone, room temperature
1/3 cup (75g) powdered sugar, sifted
1 tsp vanilla extract
INSTRUCTIONS‚Ä®Preheat the oven to 350 degrees. Line a 8-inch round cake pan with parchment paper. Grease cake pan w/ a bit of oil & dust w/ cocoa powder, set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, whisk together the dry ingredients. Add the olive oil, water & vanilla, and whisk until smooth. Drizzle vinegar over the top & stir it into the batter, until just combined. Pour batter into cake pan. Bake 40-45 minutes, until the top is gently puffed & cake tester comes out mostly clean. Remove from oven & allow to cool in pan on a rack for 30 min, then carefully run a knife around edge of the pan & invert cake onto a baking rack to cool completely.
Whisk together room temperature mascarpone cheese w/ sifted powdered sugar & vanilla extract. Spread an even layer of frosting onto cake, creating swirls & swoops w/ the spatula. Garnish w/ pomegranate arils & enjoy!
.

Dark Chocolate Olive Oil Cake with whipped mascarpone & pomegranate arils featuring @carapelliusa‚Äôs Il Centenario Extra Virgin Olive Oil #carapelliambassador
.
I absolutely love using olive oil when I bake and this chocolate cake really highlights the beauty of @carapelliusa‚Äôs artfully crafted Il Centenario. This elegant extra virgin olive oil adds a pleasant bitterness & lovely fruitiness to this rich chocolate cake. Swirls of creamy whipped mascarpone get topped with deep ruby pomegranate arils for a gorgeous seasonal garnish that is perfectly festive for the holiday season!
.
This cake really highlights the beauty of @carapelliusa‚Äôs artfully crafted olive oil & will make for such a pleasant treat to share with friends & family during the holidays. Head to the link in my profile to learn more about @carapelliusa‚Äôs line of olive oils & grab the recipe for this amazing cake below!
.
INGREDIENTS
1-1/2 cups (180g) ap flour
2/3 cup (64g) unsweetened¬†Dutch processed cocoa powder
1-1/2 tsp baking soda
1/2 tsp kosher salt
3/4 cup (144g)sugar
2/3 cup (106g) dark brown sugar
1 tbsp instant espresso powder
1/2 cup olive oil
1 cup water, at room-temperature
2 tsp¬†pure vanilla extract
1 Tbsp apple cider vinegar
12 oz. mascarpone, room temperature
1/3 cup (75g) powdered sugar, sifted
1 tsp vanilla extract
INSTRUCTIONS‚Ä®Preheat the oven to 350 degrees. Line a 8-inch round cake pan with parchment paper. Grease cake pan w/ a bit of oil & dust w/ cocoa powder, set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, whisk together the dry ingredients. Add the olive oil, water & vanilla, and whisk until smooth. Drizzle vinegar over the top & stir it into the batter, until just combined. Pour batter into cake pan. Bake 40-45 minutes, until the top is gently puffed & cake tester comes out mostly clean. Remove from oven & allow to cool in pan on a rack for 30 min, then carefully run a knife around edge of the pan & invert cake onto a baking rack to cool completely.
Whisk together room temperature mascarpone cheese w/ sifted powdered sugar & vanilla extract. Spread an even layer of frosting onto cake, creating swirls & swoops w/ the spatula. Garnish w/ pomegranate arils & enjoy!
.

REVERSE SEAR method üëäüèª The meat rest on the top floor away from the source of heat. Getting more and more tenderness,  smoke and aroma from wood chunks of used wine barrel located at the bottom of the grill close to the burners. Beneath all that goodness fresh vegetable that get the dripping of the fat with the taste of the spices. this vegetables gonna be the perfect side with special juicy taste. Just put them fresh as they are.
.
.
Use only one or two burners to stabilize the temperature around 120-140 ¬∞ C. Do not go over to 150 ¬∞ C to prevent process of searing the meat. Waiting for about two hours to reach the your internal target temperature inside the meat (use temperature probs). The For me the target temperature is  about 53-54 degrees Celsius (medium-rear). the thermometers should be placed close to the bone where it is area in the steak that harder for heat penetration. At this stage let the meat a rest of 2-3 minutes and meanwhile increase the burners to the maximum heat. 2 minutes of searing on each side, another 2-3 minutes of rest and it's ready to be your perfect steak. This is one of the only ways to achieve a same cooked and color from edge to edge by using grill only.
.

Slurpilicious homemade noodles in mushrooms ginger sauce ‚ÄòÈ¶ôËèáÁÑñÊùøÈù¢‚ÄôüòãSave this simple recipe for a perfect satisfying meal on cold weather days. Have a great & safe Tuesday, friendsü§ó
‚Å£
Recipe (yields 3-4 servings):‚Å£‚Å£‚Å£
üå±Noodle ingredients:‚Å£‚Å£‚Å£
~ 2 cups all-purpose flour‚Å£
~ 3 tablespoons aquafaba (chickpea water)/more ice water‚Å£
~ 1/4 cup + 2 tablespoons ice-cold water‚Å£
~ 1/4 tsp salt‚Å£‚Å£‚Å£
‚Å£‚úÖPlace all ingredients in a bowl & knead (with hand) into a smooth dough (mixer works too). Cover with a damp paper towel & let it rest for 30 minutes.
‚úÖDivide dough into 4 equal parts.‚Å£ Using a pasta machine, run one dough through a dough thinner a few times, then change settings to cut. Cut dough into long noodles & coat noodles well with flour to prevent from sticking. (If not using a pasta machine, roll each dough out thinly, then cut the pasta to your desired width)
‚úÖBring a pot of water with a pinch of salt to boil & cook noodles until al dente, about 3 minutes.‚Å£‚Å£
‚Å£
üå±Other ingredients:‚Å£
~ 1-2 cups veggie stock‚Å£
~ 1 cup chopped cabbage/any veggies‚Å£
~ a few caps of softened Chinese mushrooms, sliced‚Å£
~ 4 slices of ginger, 3 cloves garlic - sliced‚Å£
~ 1 tablespoon soy sauce‚Å£, 1 tablespoon stir fry sauce (homemade recipe on highlights)‚Å£
~ oil, toasted sesame oil, salt to taste, cornstarch slurry (optional)‚Å£
‚Å£‚úÖIn a heated non-stick pan with 1 teaspoon oil, saut√© ginger then mushrooms until lightly brown over low-medium heat. Continue to saut√© garlic until fragrant & season with salt/soy sauce. Then, add in veggie stock, sauces & bring it to boil.
‚úÖAdd in chopped cabbage, turn heat to low & let simmer until cabbage is fully cooked through (I like my cabbage a bit raw for the crunch). Season accordingly to your preference. For a thicker sauce, stir in the cornstarch slurry. ‚Å£
‚Å£‚úÖBefore serving, toss cooked noodles in sauce until well coated & season with a drizzle of toasted sesame oil. Enjoyüòã

Creamy Lentil Penne with Portobello Mushrooms and Collard Greens by @veganreset üíú
.
Ingredients

3 oz lentil penne (dry weight)
3 large or 4 small collard green leaves, chopped
2 green onions, chopped
1 garlic clove, minced (optional)
1 large portobello mushroom cap, chopped
1/2 tsp liquid smoke or a pinch of smoked salt (optional)
1 tsp olive oil
1/2 tsp soy or Tamari sauce (optional)
1 cup of roasted butternut cashew sauce (recipe in the notes below)
Salt to taste
Freshly ground pepper
Instructions

Boil about 2-3 cups of water in an electric kettle (or a pot)*
In a pan, saut√© the green onion, mushroom and garlic in the olive oil over medium heat for 2-3 minutes before adding the soy sauce, liquid smoke and collard greens.
Mix well, then add the lentil penne and set a timer for 9 minutes.
Add just enough boiling water to the pan to cover the penne and keep stirring. Keep an eye on the pan and add a little more boiling water each time it starts to evaporate. You‚Äôll want there to be enough liquid to cook the penne, but not too much as you won‚Äôt be draining the pasta.
At the 7 minute mark, add the butter nut sauce to the pan and reduce heat to low. Keep stirring for the remaining 2 minutes. Add salt to taste Tip: If the sauce is too thin, add a little cornstarch and if it‚Äôs too thick, add a little water.
Serve topped with freshly ground pepper and enjoy!

LASAGNE AI CARCIOFI
.
----- INGREDIENTI -----
.
6 carciofi
1 spicchio d'aglio
1/2 bicchiere d'acqua
500 ml di besciamella
1/2 bicchiere di latte
250 g di sfoglia pronta per lasagne
250 g mozzarella
200 g di prosciutto cotto a dadini o pancetta
30 g di parmigiano o formaggio grattugiato
.
----- PROCEDIMENTO -----
.
Per prima cosa puliamo i carciofi e tagliamoli a fettine sottili. In un tegame facciamo soffriggere l‚Äôaglio in olio di oliva, aggiungiamo i carciofi e facciamoli rosolare qualche minuto mescolando spesso.

Aggiungiamo il sale, mezzo bicchiere d‚Äôacqua, copriamo con il coperchio e lasciamo cuocere 20 minuti. Se necessario aggiungiamo altra acqua durante la cottura.

Nel frattempo prepariamo la besciamella oppure possiamo acquistarla gi√† pronta.
Se √® troppo soda aggiungiamo mezzo bicchiere di latte per renderla pi√π liquida, faciliter√† la cottura della sfoglia.

Se invece usiamo una sfoglia classica non serve allungare la besciamella, ma dovremmo sbollentare la pasta prima di usarla per la lasagna.

Tagliamo a cubetti sia la mozzarella che il prosciutto cotto.

Prendiamo una pirofila, sul fondo spalmiamo uno strato di besciamella, formiamo una strato di sfoglia, poi sopra altra besciamella.

Quindi distribuiamo carciofi, mozzarella e prosciutto cotto, aggiungiamo una spolverata di parmigiano grattugiato.

Procediamo con una nuova sfoglia e continuiamo fino a finire la sfoglia, il ripieno e la besciamella. Inforniamo a 190¬∞C oppure in forno ventilato a 180¬∞C e lasciamo cuocere per 30-35 minuti.

So I just stumbled upon this gem in the basement of #DunmanFoodCentre. I had already inhaled a plate of my favourite #joochiatahhuatwantonnoodle but was feeling greedy, so at the spur of the moment, decided to try food from this stall.
There were only a few dishes on display but somehow, I had an inkling they were going to taste very good. I was right. The two items I ordered - #sambalgoreng and the mix of paru (cow‚Äôs lung) with daging (beef) sambal were truly aromatic and delicious. If you have never enjoyed paru because you thought it‚Äôs too hard and chewy, the one here will be a revelation in spongey softness. But it‚Äôs not just that. The rempah (blend of spices) of both dishes are drool-worthy. Even the splash of #sayurlodeh gravy on my rice was wonderfully fragrant and thick-ish.
I chatted briefly to the young Malay lady who owns this stall and she said although she has walk-in customers, the bulk of her business is catering. There is a Whatsapp number on her @daunlimaurecipes account for orders to be placed if you are keen to try. And I do think if you are like me and enjoy rich, spicy Malay food, you should. She does hers really well.

From tender Iberico pork slices to poached salmon topped with blow-torched mentaiko, @IshiroSG's Japanese rice bowls are all priced affordably (from S$7.90 to S$10.90) and all come with an onsen egg and fluffy Japanese rice. Its newest outlet is at China Square Central, which is in the Telok Ayer area, perfect for the working crowd. I'd recommend the Ishiro Chasu Bowl (S$8.90)---the pork belly slices were thick and juicy, and had been steeped in a soy-based marinade prior to being cooked, so each bite was gloriously salty and savoury. Ishiro also has outlets at Republic Polytechic, Nanyang Polytechnic and Pearl Hill, so be sure to check it out! ~@coexhale

Cavolo cappuccio verde con speck e pinoli
.
‚û°Ô∏èIdeale per il pranzo al lavoro, accompagnando con pane integrale, crackers o grissini.
.
Per 1 persona:
Un quarto di cavolo cappuccio
50 g di speck sgrassato
2 cucchiai di pinoli (circa 15 g, sostituiscono le 3 noci giornaliere)
Olio evo
Pepe un pizzico
Aceto bianco qb
Pane g 50-80
.
Procedimento

Appassite il cavolo tagliato a listarelle sottili alcuni minuti in padella con pepe e aceto bianco, poi unite lo speck a straccetti e i pinoli e saltate ancora qualche minuto. Aggiungete l'olio alla fine. Non serve aggiungere sale.
Potete sostituire i pinoli con le noci.
.
Informazioni nutrizionali

Piatto ricco di proteine animali (speck), grassi buoni (olio e pinoli), fibre (cavolo), carboidrati complessi (crackers o grissini o pane integrale meglio ancora).
.

Cassoni con cime di rapa

Le cime di rapa, dopo averle mondate e lavate accuratamente, sbollentatele in acqua salata per 7-8 minuti. Scolate, strizzate e saltate in padella con olio, peperoncino e aglio. 
I cassoni sono fatti con la piadina all'olio e ricotta. Formate delle piadine, farcitele con le cime di rapa poi richiudete premendo sui bordi con i rebbi della forchetta per farli chiudere bene.

Ricetta

Piadina all'olio e ricotta

Per 8-10 piadine 
500 g di farina 0 (si pu√≤ mischiare con della farina integrale)
Olio di semi 1 bicchiere
Latte parzialmente scremato 1 bicchiere e mezzo circa
Sale qb
1 pizzico di bicarbonato
Ricotta vaccina g 120

Fare la fontana con la farina, nel mezzo versare l'olio, la ricotta, il sale e il bicarbonato e impastare.

Rifare la fontana con l'impasto, nel mezzo versare un po' alla volta il latte in modo da controllare la consistenza dell'impasto. Alla fine deve risultare abbastanza sodo. Non deve essere appiccicoso.
Se usate la farina integrale, cambiano le quantit√† di liquidi.

Gamberi alla paprika su letto di radicchio spadellato

Per una persona:
Mezza palla di radicchio
200-230 g di gamberetti (peso lordo)
Spezie a piacere
Aceto balsamico qb
Vino bianco qb
Olio evo qb
Pane integrale g 50-80

Fate appassire il radicchio in padella con olio e un pizzico di sale, poi spadellate con aceto balsamico.

I gamberetti li sbollentate due minuti in acqua salata, poi li private della parte esterna, li sfumate con vino bianco poi saltate qualche minuto con generosa paprika affumicata/dolce e peperoncino in polvere, finch√© non si sar√† formata una bella crosticina.
Giro d'olio sul finale.

Servite con del pane integrale o grissini e una salsina a base di yogurt se vi piace.

Falafel di ceci

Per una o due persone:

250 g di ceci cotti o 80 g secchi
Mezza cipolla bianca
1 spicchio d'aglio (facoltativo)
2 cni di olio evo
Un mazzetto di prezzemolo
1-2 cucchiaini di curry
Una spolverata di paprika dolce
5-6 semini di cumino
Sale e pepe qb
1-2 cucchiai di farina di ceci o pangrattato, se necessario

Tamponate bene i ceci dopo averli risciacquati, in modo da eliminare tutta l'umidit√†.
Se usate quelli secchi (bisognerebbe!!!) dovete metterli in ammollo per 12 ore, scolarli, tamponarli e frullarli direttamente, senza cottura.
.
‚û°Ô∏èPer preparare i falafel √® indicato usare i ceci secchi!
.
Frullate poi i ceci con tutti gli ingredienti. Se l'impasto risultasse troppo umido, aggiungete la farina di ceci o il pangrattato.
.
‚û°Ô∏èFormate i falafel, dovreste ottenerne 10. Lasciate riposare in frigo un'ora se andrete a cuocerli in padella oliata. Attenzione che l'olio non sia bollente altrimenti si sfalderanno.
.
‚û°Ô∏èIo consiglio invece la cottura in forno statico a 200¬∞ per una ventina di minuti, risulteranno croccantissimi! Questa cottura √® ovviamente pi√π sana e consigliata nel caso risultassero troppo morbidi, in padella si sfalderebbero completamente.
.
Porzione
Questo piatto √® a base di ceci con l'aggiunta di olio, quindi la porzione pu√≤ essere la ricetta intera, cotta al forno, associando un contorno, con o senza pane a seconda delle esigenze di ognuno.
Oppure met√† ricetta a persona, se cotte in padella (perch√© aumentano il potere calorico andando ad assorbire l'olio di cottura) con un contorno e una porzione di carboidrati, pi√π o meno a seconda delle esigenze.

Gnocchi di patate e barbabietola rossa, ricetta per 6 persone

Ingredienti:
1 kg di patate (peso lordo)
150 gr di barbabietola rossa cotta (pesata cotta)
Sale, pepe
Pizzico di cannella
1 uovo medio
Farina 0 gr 300 o pi√π

Cuocete le patate, io le ho cotte a vapore in pentola pressione per 8 minuti, tagliate a fette e senza buccia. Lasciatele poi raffreddare completamente, questo permetter√† di lavorare meglio l'impasto. Una volta fredde passatele nello schiaccia patate, lavorando su una spianatoia. Polpette di lenticchie e spinaci

Ingredienti per 10-12 polpette medie o 3-4 burger:
.

Spinaci freschi gr 150

Le lenticchie decorticate vanno cotte per una ventina di minuti in poca acqua, salata sul finale, poi strizzate bene. Potete asciugarle in padella se necessario.

PANDORO ALL'ARANCIA SENZA LIEVITAZIONE üçä lo fate in 5 MINUTI con una FORCHETTA e SENZA BURRO, √® SOFFICE e profumatissimo üòç un‚Äôidea VELOCISSIMA per preparare un dolce NATALIZIO in poco tempo e con ZERO sbattimento üòÅ

Ingredienti:
300 g di farina 00
175 g di zucchero
125 g di olio di semi
100 g di succo di arancia + scorza grattugiata
50 g di fecola di patate
4 uova
una bustina di lievito per dolci
vaniglia q.b.

zucchero a velo q.b.

Procedimento:
Mettete le uova all'interno di una ciotola, aggiungete lo zucchero, la scorza grattugiata d'arancia, la vaniglia e sbattete energicamente il tutto con una forchetta. Versate l'olio e mescolate. Aggiungete anche il succo di arancia. Incorporate la farina, la fecola di patate, il lievito e lavorate tutti gli ingredienti sempre con la forchetta fino ad ottenere un impasto omogeneo e senza grumi. Oleate (o imburrate) ed infarinate l'interno dello stampo del pandoro e versate il composto al suo interno. Cuocete la torta pandoro all'arancia veloce senza lievitazione in forno preriscaldato a 180 gradi per circa 45 minuti. Il pandoro all'arancia √® pronto, capovolgetelo su di una gratella, fatelo raffreddare, sformatelo e ricopritelo con abbondante zucchero a velo.

Roasted Chickpeas and Avocado Toast by @twospoons.ca üíö
.

1 can (400 ml) chickpeas 
1/2 tsp paprika
2 tsp olive oil, plus more to drizzle
pinch sea salt
1 avocado
2 slices sourdough bread, 1-inch thick
sea salt and pepper
.
.
1. Preheat oven to 400F/200C. Strain chickpeas and pat dry. Toss into a mixing bowl with paprika, olive oil and a generous pinch of sea salt. Mix to combine. Line a baking tray with parchment paper and pour chickpeas onto tray. Bake in oven for 5 minutes, or until lightly brown and sizzling.
2. Toast two slices sourdough bread. Scoop avocado onto bread and gently press down with a fork to mash and spread even. Sprinkle with sea salt and pepper. Top toast with roasted chickpeas. Optional to sprinkle with more sea salt, pepper and cayenne pepper. Lightly drizzle with olive oil. #bestofvegan

Crispy tofu stir-fry with mushrooms and French green beans in Korean BBQ sauce by @cookingforpeanuts üß°
.
Press and dry 1-14oz block extra-firm tofu with heavy object and paper towels to remove excess liquid. Cut into bite-size cubes. Toss with some low-sodium tamari or soy sauce to lightly coat each cube. Place 3 tbsp corn starch into a freezer bag and add tofu cubes. Seal bag and shake until tofu pieces are coated with the corn starch. Make Korean BBQ sauce: In medium bowl, mix 3/4 cup low-sodium tamari or soy sauce, 3 tbsp maple syrup, 1/4 cup water, 1 tbsp rice vinegar, 1-1/2 tbsp chili paste (or to taste), 2 tsp sesame oil, 1 tsp finely minced ginger, 5 finely minced garlic cloves. In a small bowl, mix 1 tbsp cornstarch in 1 tbsp water until dissolved. Set bowls aside. Heat a little neutral oil in non-stick skillet. Add 1 lb cremini mushrooms (thickly sliced), flat side down, and let sit a few minutes before disturbing. Once bottom is dark golden-brown, saut√© and cook until both sides are the same color. Add a splash of tamari or soy sauce and cook 30 seconds. Transfer to flat plate. Add 1 lb cut French green beans to skillet and saut√© until dark golden-brown. Transfer to plate with mushrooms. Add more oil if needed and saut√© coated tofu until all sides are golden. Transfer mushrooms and green beans back into skillet with tofu. Pour sauce into a small saucepan. Bring to a gentle boil while whisking. Add the dissolved cornstarch and keep whisking. Heat while whisking until starts to thicken. Spoon desired amount of sauce into skillet with tofu and veggies. Mix well to incorporate while gently heating. Refrigerate leftover sauce. #bestofvegan

Comforting Black Bean Chili by @healthylivingjames üß°

Ingredients *  2 tbsp olive oil *  3 garlic cloves crushed *  1 small red onion diced *  1/2 tsp ground coriander *  1 tsp paprika *  1/2 tsp cayenne pepper *  1/2 tsp cinnamon *  1 red chilli deseeded and diced *  2 large carrots grated *  680 g passata good quality *  2 tbsp tomato puree *  2 (400g) cans black beans drained and rinsed *  1 (400g) can kidney beans drained and rinsed *  1 tbsp cacao powder (optional) *  200 ml veg stock good quality

Instructions *
Start by grating the carrot, dicing the red onion and fresh chilli *
Heat a large pan on a medium heat adding the olive oil and garlic until sizzling *
Add the onion and all the spices along with a pinch of salt and pepper and stir *
Now add the carrots and chopped chilli and cook down for 2-3 minutes until soft *
Add the passata, tomato puree, beans, cacao powder and stock and stir *
Bring to a boil and then reduce to a low/medium heat to cook for 15 minutes (making sure to stir every 5 minutes). Serving suggestion: with baked sweet potatoes, vegan sour cream or yogurt & fresh herbs. #bestofvegan

VEGAN S‚ÄôMORE TRUFFLES by @itsallgoodvegan ‚ù§Ô∏è
.
S‚Äômore Truffles
2 cups graham crackers, (I used vegan cinnamon graham)
8 medjool dates, soaked in warm water
2 Tbsp maple or agave syrup
¬Ω cup almond butter, or your favorite nut butter
12 mini vegan marshmallows
1 cup chopped vegan chocolate
1 Tbsp coconut oil
.
Directions:
Place your graham crackers in a food processor or high powered blender and pulse until your graham crackers have turned into fine crumbs. Combine the graham cracker crumbs,soaked dates, almond butter, and syrup to the food processor or high powered blender. Process again until it becomes a sticky cookie dough like texture. Using a small cookie scoop place 1 tablespoon of the dough in the cookie scoop and press down. The dough should be packed lining the scooper. Place the mini marshmallow in the middle of packed cookie dough scoop. Place another tablespoon of dough on top of the marshmallow. Using your fingers press the mixture down forming a ball. Remove the dough from the cookie scoop. Using your hands form the truffle into a firm ball. Set S‚Äômore dough balls on a plate and repeat steps. Make the chocolate coating. Combine the chocolate and coconut oil in a microwave-safe bowl. Microwave for 30 second intervals stirring between each one until the chocolate has melted. Coat each dough ball with chocolate. I used a fork to do this. Place truffles on a plate and top with crushed graham crackers or marshmallows. Place in the refrigerator for 30 minutes to harden. #bestofvegan
